Class ConceptVuforiaUltimateGoalNavigation

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.qualcomm.robotcore.eventloop.opmode.OpMode
      • com.qualcomm.robotcore.eventloop.opmode.LinearOpMode
        • org.firstinspires.ftc.robotcontroller.external.samples.ConceptVuforiaUltimateGoalNavigation
  • @TeleOp(name="ULTIMATEGOAL Vuforia Nav",
        group="Concept")
@Disabled
public class ConceptVuforiaUltimateGoalNavigation
extends com.qualcomm.robotcore.eventloop.opmode.LinearOpMode
    This 2020-2021 OpMode illustrates the basics of using the Vuforia localizer to determine positioning and orientation of robot on the ULTIMATE GOAL FTC field. The code is structured as a LinearOpMode

    When images are located, Vuforia is able to determine the position and orientation of the image relative to the camera. This sample code then combines that information with a knowledge of where the target images are on the field, to determine the location of the camera.

    From the Audience perspective, the Red Alliance station is on the right and the Blue Alliance Station is on the left.

    There are a total of five image targets for the ULTIMATE GOAL game. Three of the targets are placed in the center of the Red Alliance, Audience (Front), and Blue Alliance perimeter walls. Two additional targets are placed on the perimeter wall, one in front of each Tower Goal. Refer to the Field Setup manual for more specific location details

    A final calculation then uses the location of the camera on the robot to determine the robot's location and orientation on the field.

    See Also:
    VuforiaLocalizer, see ultimategoal/doc/tutorial/FTC_FieldCoordinateSystemDefinition.pdf Use Android Studio to Copy this Class, and Paste it into your team's code folder with a new name. Remove or comment out the @Disabled line to add this opmode to the Driver Station OpMode list. IMPORTANT: In order to use this OpMode, you need to obtain your own Vuforia license key as is explained below.
